reviews.text: Food was decent. The service was good. I enjoyed the 50's music. I plan to go back again.
I love this place!! Old fashioned burger diner feeling and the service is always great. The owner is a fantastic person!
Food was OK but not great but the price was ridiculous. Way to expensive for the amount and type of food you got.
What great service! And amazing food! I've been coming here for years and it's hands down my favorite little burger spot.
Always excellent. Always friendly staff. Always 5 Star.

Lovely tea service and friendly atmosphere. Like a diner and family restaurant but more refined and still quaint. Adorable place, good for family groups and just going with a friend. If you're going by yourself I recommend bringing a book or something to write with. Lots of subtle inspiration brimming over here.

We love Breadboard, it's our favorite  place for breakfast. Everything we've eaten there has been great. My husband loves the Breadboard omelet and my favorite is the Calico Special. The berry jam is awesome!
The staff were very friendly and welcoming. The food was delicious as well. I completly recommend the mountain man.

Awesome Eggs Benedict - Eggs were poached to perfection....Homers were dating bomb. 

I am a fan for sure!

🤗
Wow! Wonderful service, fantastic food, decent prices & we received our order fast!
Very good! Perfect amount and the price is great
Amazing food. Bao are soft and fluffy and the pork filling is very flavorful. Bento is good and portions are generous. Great spot for a quick snack or lunch. No indoor seating and cash only.

Oh my goodness this place is YUMMY!! I ate it so quick I forgot to take a before picture! They make an amazing peanut sauce and pour it over a couple cups of white or brown rice and a few skewers of chicken! They also have steak too!! 

All for under $7!  

It’s a bit hidden but if you want the best bento in Ashland then you’ll find this place worth it!!

PS: I went back a few days after this and finally got a before picture! Just look at how great this looks!

Love this place- however... I was disappointed that Stanley raised the price of the Indonesian chicken sate by a dollar. $6.75 is slightly steep for 3 small skewers, rice and peanut sauce. The original price at $5.75 was much more accommodating  and affordable for a walk in establishment such as Bentos. For $7 I might as well go to a real restaurant
This place is a hidden gem in Ashland

I tried their blackberry Oregon ribs and I highly recommend this item. The meat was rich and tender, and the blackberry sauce complemented it well. I also had the Caesar salad, which was good. Service was also prompt and friendly. I visited on a Friday afternoon, and it was pretty empty at the time.

Have been coming here off and on for 3 years. Good food, good prices, great friendly and attentive staff, clean and relaxing atmosphere with nice music that is unobtrusive. Having all of these things at once is definitely a rare combination these days!
Great service, great food.  Very attentive staff.  Glad we stopped in.  I had a hamburger with the gluten free option.  My wife had fish and chips.
Great food, but small place. Get there before it gets too busy! Great location of right downtown and right by lithia park
Really great food and very affordable. The service was amazing and we felt welcomed. Definitely a favorite of mine.
Great fresh food, they remember you and what you usually have. Reasonable price for lunch or casual dinner. Convenient.
Really good sandwiches. Soft bread and just delicious. But if you're looking for large amounts of meat I wouldn't suggest it.
Yummy sandwiches and fast service with a smile
The sandwich was delicious was our first time there. Service was awesome and the owner was friendly
AWESOME glad. Fresh ingredients and the softest bread EVER! Staff is AMAZING!

The people are friendly and loving. The food is awesome and healing,... I like having healthy food that is made from the heart and the soul. Pita, pita ..bread and all kinds of Mediterranean, food is the best diet for me.  I am treated very well and helped with regards to my disabilities. I don't feel like a stranger at Pita Pita. My friends with disabilities, who are  able to take out food or eat inside the restaurant, please try the food and you will feel good after eating. They fill your stomach with good food and they fill your heart and soul with a warmth and Welcome that is remembered even when you're plate is empty.

Some of the best Mediterranean food I've had, and I've been to a fair few Mediterranean countries. The staff is always friendly and wonderful, and they renovated the restaurant a couple years ago; it looks amazing.

They also cater, and were incredibly efficient and professional with the whole process.
This is by far the best chicken ever!  The service is always fast and friendly.  I also recommend this place.  P.s you have to try the garlic spread

Great food, great service, enjoyed the experience. If it's your first time and you've never had this style of food I'd recommend bringing a friend and getting the platter. ( There is a vegetarian option for it)
Friendly staff, but food was very lackluster. I ordered a beef gyro and they microwave reheated what tasted like slow cooker beef. I expected fresh kabob.
a well designed and functional open kitchen prepares well cooked and seasoned food.  nicely appointed.  good coffee. nice vibes permeate ...

Outstanding, local farm fresh, made in-house deliciousness. Drinks were on point. I had a sour beer, kale salad, cauliflower soup & fresh fried chicken w/ hot honey and a side of house made ranch dressing that paired perfectly w/ the juicy fried chicken. Had a relaxing time sitting on the porch and with the nice pace of our plates coming to the table, we were able to really enjoy ourselves. Thank you, Hither! We'll return, perhaps for brunch!

I am always looking forward to my next experience at Hither! The food is very creative and super delicious! Their coffee is top notch too if you're a real aficionado. If you get the chance try one of their special wine paired dinners, just do it!  We're planning to attend the chocolate inspired five-course dinner with wine pairings this March.  Separately, they have holiday offerings too. My family ordered a pre-dressed Carman Ranch dry aged prime rib last December and wow... was it good!

I loved my lunch - A Crepe with Brie,Spinach, Bacon ,and Fried Egg.
Soo delicious!!!
I can't wait to go there and have  dinner.
Hither is exquisite. The herbed eggs were superb and the employees are beautifully helpful and kind. Five stars!! I’ll be coming back!!
Cute restaurant and good servers. The iced tea is wonderful! The breakfast burrito was bland. The crepes were very rich but yummy.

Extremely comfortable with welcoming and excellent service. Delicious food and good portion sizes. I dont know if I have ever had faster food service especially when ordering eggs Benedict. Seriously I feel like it took less than 10 minutes! The cooks appeared happy and like they were having fun and enjoyed their jobs, that definitely carried over to the food!

Loved it! It was our 3rd restaurant we had tired to order lunch as the 1st 2 were out of what we wanted.  We ordered the albacore tuna melt with hand cut fries. It was totally enough to share. The melt was delicious and service was friendly and fast. We'll definitely be back. Their breakfast items looked amazing and enough to share if you can.

We stopped in for lunch today. We ordered salads & I had a cup of their chicken & rice soup. Salads were very good with plenty of flavors besides the dressings. The soup was delicious with plenty of flavor and chicken galore! We will definitely come again.
Really good food, decent coffee. Place was packed and we still received our food in a very short time. 10 out of 10 would do again.

Went in for date night Friday. We were seated quickly. The place was very busy. We sat in the back that had a view of Ashland Creek. Wait staff was efficient. My Fiance had the pesto fettuccine with chicken, I had the chef salad. Decent portions. My Fiance loved her dish and was only able to eat half. My salad was loaded, very tasty and completely filled me up. The iced tea was good too. Definitely worth the price for what you receive.

What a perfect day for lunch beside the creek in Ashland! I had the special chicken salad wrap with a glass of delicious ice tea. The wrap was fresh, my server kindly asked if the side of avocado I asked for should be included inside the wrap. She was friendly and wonderful!
Classic hometown diner.  Wonderful generous breakfast.  Attentive staff.  I had the Ashlandistan omelette.  It was 3” tall full of vegetables and probably two potatoes worth of  breakfast potatoes.

Nice little spot, we've only ever been there for lunch, but food is fresh and well made. Nothing fancy or exotic but everything we've ever ordered when stopping in has been tasty and prepared as ordered. The garlic ranch is very good.
Great service,  good food.  The coffee is good, dark roast in a hot cup.  Perfect.

I tried their blackberry Oregon ribs and I highly recommend this item. The meat was rich and tender, and the blackberry sauce complemented it well. I also had the Caesar salad, which was good. Service was also prompt and friendly. I visited on a Friday afternoon, and it was pretty empty at the time.

Have been coming here off and on for 3 years. Good food, good prices, great friendly and attentive staff, clean and relaxing atmosphere with nice music that is unobtrusive. Having all of these things at once is definitely a rare combination these days!
Great service, great food.  Very attentive staff.  Glad we stopped in.  I had a hamburger with the gluten free option.  My wife had fish and chips.
Great food, but small place. Get there before it gets too busy! Great location of right downtown and right by lithia park
Really great food and very affordable. The service was amazing and we felt welcomed. Definitely a favorite of mine.

Passing through on a long drive home, stopped to stretch our legs and wound up here for lunch. Absolutely the most delicious panini I have ever put in my mouth!! (“Eat Your Heart Out”) 

Reasonable price, clean restaurant & service was on point. I’m wondering if there’s a location near me. If not, may return next time we’re passing through. Worth another visit!
Delicious fresh and organic wraps soups & paninis. Was a super delight finding a healthy lunch that didn’t lack in flavor

The wrap....Not that good
(It was the teriyaki chicken wrap...I'm from Hawaii and half Japanese sorry)
the soups are wonderful. 
The help service awesome with Ashland charm.

OMG Best corn chowder I've ever had!
Stopped at this place while traveling and I'm happy I did. The guy was super nice and helpful, the place is very cute and clean.
After eating my cup of chowder I bought a quart for the road.  It's really outstanding.

Casual, small. Order at the counter, food is brought to the table. Great soups & wraps, a couple of salads, but any wrap can be made into a salad instead. Large portions. Gluten-free wraps & cookies available. Vegan & vegetarian options. Everything is made there from scratch. Delicious! Also great staff.
The food was overpriced and mediocre. The service was very slow. I wouldn't recommend it since there are several other good options close by.
A great breakfast place! Lots of delicious options. The atmosphere is warm, inviting and friendly. The service staff is very friendly and attentive. We all enjoyed our meals!

The best breakfast I've been in over a decade and one of the best establishments I've ever been too . This restaurant is a poster child for what a breakfast place should be. I am envious that this business does not belong to me it has been tuned to run well . The quality of the food ,portions the freshness the variety  the value balance for all was absolutely excellent. They are always bussy here and after eating here I understand now why.  I am sold . Whenever I'm in the area and make sure to go there . I was just sitting here writing this review and I really wish I was there right now.

Love this place.  Been coming for years now.  Price is high but the quality reflects it.  Haven't had anything I didn't like.  I'm more of a traditionalist but enjoy the alternating specials.  The wait can be long, especially on weekends, plan accordingly.

Had a great experience here having a late Monday morning breakfast. Quickly seated, quickly served, friendly staff. The blueberry sourdough pancakes was the standout dish. Definitely will be having that again next time.

Incredibly good breakfast food. It will quickly get rather busy in the mornings. Our party ordered: Lemon blueberry pancakes, Lemon ricotta French toast, a Chicken sausage spinach mushroom and Brie omelette and a Steak with caramelized onion omelette. Every single dish was fantastic, and the muffins alongside the meals were delicious as well. I want to eat here every morning. Each dish was about 14-15 dollars or so. Well worth the money.

Good food, good service. The salad is cut very largely and I wish that they had more dressing options because I hate the one they have. 
Del Rio wine, so that's great. The pastas are all delicious, but don't expect any leftovers. 
The brownie, especially a la mode, is incredible. Their take out lasagna is also really great.

THE BEST BREAD THAT I HAVE EVER HAD, EVER! So good, in fact, that I bought a loaf to take home! Quaint, friendly, healthy! Also THE BEST vinaigrette that I have ever had EVER, too! I wish I lived in Ashland just so I could dine here often. There is NOTHING like this in my town, sadly! Homemade quality- yum! Easy to please vegan needs!

Now serving brunch on weekends -- and one of the best brunches I've had in Ashland. Great service, friendly staff and owner. Excited to go back and try their normal fare during the week. If it's this good, I may have found my new favorite Italian place.

Wiley has enlarged and reinvented his World in the last year ... and with a very good result. The food is just as good, and no less affordable. Honest ingredients generously and skillfully prepared by a skilled chef and cheerfully served by Southern Oregon University co-eds. Our salads were interesting, not the same-old-same-old iceberg and pseudo-tomato. The special -- we always go for the special! -- Oregon Bay shrimp over fettuccini in a sherry cream sauce, was delicious, the pasta exactly on point and the sauce rich but not unctuous. Luckily, we still had room for Wiley's delicious light chocolate mousse. In a town with puffed-up eateries intended to fleece the play-goers, Wiley's is worth a short trip uptown. We're so glad we found it, years ago, and you can bet we'll be back.

I'm surprised to see so many good reviews because the place they are describing is not the place I saw, I went there on a Friday night, wasn't very busy. The place didn't look bad, the sign said they were organic but who really knows. The lady who seated us seemed nice, but when we sat down at our table, it was wobbly, I even said something and the lady who seated us noticed, but didn't reseat us, apologize, or even try to find a solution. I ordered some sort of sausage ravioli, my girlfriend ordered salmon ravioli and it was all definitely frozen, even the sauce tasted like it was from a jar. Our waiter seemed nice and that is the only reason I'm giving this place a 2 stars. Maybe everyone else was drinking because our experience was not good at all.

Amuse never disappoints! Fantastic food and even better service in a relaxing and romantic environment. If you are looking for a great place for date night, this is the place to go. Highly recommended!

Best food in Ashland. Delicious fresh salads, entrees and desserts to die for. We sat outdoors and enjoyed a very quiet dinner, even though the restaurant was completely full. Great service! Highly recommend.
Food is amazing. If you go on Thursday they have a 3 course dinner for under $45 great deal for this caliber of restaurant.
White Table Cloths do not a Fine Dining Establishment Make! Same as Raw Fish isn't always Sushi Grade, but here, all the right elements combine to enhance the Experience and Reward the Senses....

Five course meal served in a contemporary setting. We made reservations three months in advance and the service did not disappoint. For theater patrons the staff ensures the meal is paced so that you can enjoy the food without being rushed.
Jonathan was super helpful and made our night. Outstanding service great food, and an enjoyable time. Highly recommended.
Great value and quality, good people running the show, great cook/kitchen staff... it is our home away from home!

I have eaten at the Dragonfly 3 times in the past several years. They have a marvelous ambience, the garden dining is well landscaped and very pleasant, the food is excellent, and the service is awful. My first bad experience was years ago, I don't recall the 2nd time, so say it was ok, and lets get to today.  Today my wife and I arrived at 12:30 pm with a 1:30 play time at the nearby Oregon Shakespeare Festival. No one admitted once the performance starts. I told the waitress this when we were seated, in part because the menu itself said service was slow due to the excellence of their food preparation. Notify the waitress if you have a deadline, it suggested, and "we'll try to accomodate you." Considering that they are two blocks from the Shakespeare theaters which are the major tourist draw of the town, you'd think that they understood theater deadlines. Still, with a 45 minute window to get a meal, it looked like a shoo-in. The more so as I ordered a cup of soup of the day - how long could that take? - and my wife ordered a tamale with no options. Thirty minutes later, at 1 p.m., no food. We had to leave at 1:15 to reach our theater seats, so I told the waitress bring the bill, we're going. She assured me that the food was coming right up, and within 2 or 3 minutes it appeared. We had 12 minutes to enjoy their specially excellent food preparation. So lunch filled our physical needs for food but not our esthetic needs for time to enjoy the pleasures of eating it. It can not take 30 minutes to make a tamale and pour a cup of soup, and their service is so routinely slow that they have to warn you on the menu. Astonishing. I suggest you only go to the Dragonfly when you are not yet hungry and have nothing on your agenda for a couple of hours. Don't worry, you'll be hungry before you get served.

Eugene, I had the SAME experience at Dragonfly. I actually read your review twice thinking I had already reviewed this restaurant. They actually chastised me and insinuated that I had no idea what I was talking about when I said my play started at 1:30pm, telling me instead that it started at 2:00pm. First, they were wrong to correct me in the way that they did upon me asking if my food would appear before my play as I had already been waiting an hour, then they were wrong to tell me the wrong time. What if I had believed them and then missed my play? A table of 3, that's three play tickets at $90 per ticket -- i.e. a lot more expensive than lunch at this inconsistent and rude restaurant.
Yummy food from Isabelle Cruz's cookbook
Great service and delicious food! We had tuna salad, calamari and pizza. Fabulous! They have gluten free options too!

The worst restaurant hands down in which I had the misfortune of dining. I give it one star only because it was the only restaurant open at the time we were in town. I asked to taste a wine as there were not many available by the glass and was not familiar with the particular one they were serving by the glass. The waitress told me that there was a regulation and she could not give me free alcohol! The food could not even make up for the bad service. The bread was hard and dry. She brought some aoili in a small dish and then charged us for it. I need to stop. Don't even go there, even if it is the only restaurant open. There is a Starbucks really close.
We love this Italian oven centric rustic style menu. Outdoor patio when the weather is nice. Great staff, the best being....Jesus. I kid you not.
Delicious everything! Mushroom pizza is absolutely amazing! Then holy cow that lemon cheesecake was DELICIOUS
Nice place for a pasta dinner or something else. We enjoyed our dinner and the ambience.
The food was really good with organic ingredients and fresh veggies. The service was good too!
Calamari tough and chewy, spring mix laced with pieces that have turned, garlic shrimp over salted and shrimp mushy. Cucumber salad was ok.
Server was very nice but the food was certainly overpriced for its quality.. Pretty salty and also $10 for an appetizer of spring rolls seemed pretty outrageous..

Went here for a holiday party. The staff was great, lots of patience and super kind. The only thing that I liked from their food though was the steak, everything else tasted like they lost either spice rack.. totally bland..

Tiger rolls. This is the only place that has them anywhere and they are heavenly. Awesome outdoor seating overlooking the creek. Prices are higher than they should be but they cater to the tourist clientele/one time dinner guest. Very busy venue. Reservations recommended.

This was such a great deal (the month of February is off season) at $105/night that I truly was not expecting much out of this stay. Wow, this ended up becoming one of the best stays I’ve ever had. The room was amazing, with just about every amenity (including bath robes, kettle to boil water for tea, etc) one can think of. Everything was immaculate and the bed was divine. There were even fresh pastries in the room. If it had ended right there, I would already have given 5 stars. But wait, they provide complimentary breakfast and it was truly one of the best breakfast I’ve ever had. Everything is freshly made and I asked for extra poached eggs on the side, and didn’t even get charged for it. Service was absolutely amazing, and Rachel was very attentive and accommodating. As if that all wasn’t enough, after I checked out, I was even offered the kitchen sink to wash out my dirty coffee bottle (I left it in the car overnight). I’m so, so impressed with the entire experience. I wish I could give it 10 stars.

Superb service all around. The bar and restaurant close before the plays are over at least in this part of the season. Great prices on happy hour at the bar. Room was clean and had treats and turn down service. Carpet could use a shampoo clean. Our bed was a bit jiggly  when one of us rolled over, but not unusual for a mattress over springs. Food in bar and breakfast were 3-4 stars, better last time we stayed a year ago. But good atmosphere and exceptional service. Location is perfect, 2 blocks walk to the playhouses and on a quiet street. Plenty of parking. We will be back to Winchester every year.

The Winchester Inn is a special place in this special town. Winchester Inn is a combination of two Victorian homes converted into an Inn.  With a world-class restaurant it is located in beautiful downtown Ashland and all that goes with that.  The rooms are spacious with high quality furnishings, beds and linens. The staff is exceptional and there are many unique services such as the turndown service and fresh baked treats every day in your room adds to the experience. The breakfast is a culinary experience rarely available anywhere.
Lovely room, very customer service oriented, everyone was helpful and friendly, the included breakfast was delicious!
Magical place to stay!  Rooms are amazing.  Breakfast included.  Dickens Feast was a blast!  Highly reccomend this wonder hotel.  5 stars from us!!!!

Revise: A local told me to give you guys another chance because you can only control certain aspects of a restaurant and I understand that.  Me after 19 years of working in the restaurant industry understand that more clearly now.

We visited from out of town and had an amazing Valentine's dinner! Exactly what we hoped for! Perfect date night! We felt as if we were special guests from host to bartenders to waitress and the table busser! Of course thank you to the chef and cook's as the food was amazing!
Great food the salmon was perfect. Great wine list. Great service and atmosphere.

reviews.author_name: What to do in Southern Oregon
reviews.text: What a wonderful experience!  The service was impeccable, food was delicious, and ambience was beautiful without being pretentious.  We look forward to many more meals here!
Great food. Drink prices are a bit high. Overall worth your time.
